Here's a step-by-step guide to creating a Discord bot using JavaScript and the discord.js library:

**Prerequisites:**

1. **Node.js**: You need to have Node.js installed on your system. You can download it from the official Node.js website.
2. **Discord.js**: You need to install the discord.js library. You can do this by running the following command in your terminal: `npm install discord.js@14`

**Creating a new bot project:**

1. Create a new folder for your bot project.
2. Initialize a new Node.js project by running `npm init` in your bot folder.
3. Create a new JavaScript file, e.g., `index.js`, and add the following code to it:
```javascript
const { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require('discord.js');

// Create a new client instance
const client = new Client({
  intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds, GatewayIntentBits.Messages]
});

// Login to Discord with your bot token
client.login('YOUR_BOT_TOKEN');
```
Replace `YOUR_BOT_TOKEN` with your actual bot token.

**Setting up a new bot application in the Discord developer portal:**

1. Go to the [Discord developer portal](https://discord.com/developers/applications).
2. Click on "New Application" and create a new application.
3. Give your application a name and click "Create".
4. Click on "Bot" and then "Add Bot" to create a new bot user.
5. Click on the "Edit" button next to your bot user and copy the "Token" value.

**Writing code for a Discord bot using Discord.js v14:**

1. Add the following code to your `index.js` file:
```javascript
const { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require('discord.js');

// Create a new client instance
const client = new Client({
  intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds, GatewayIntentBits.Messages]
});

// Event listener for messages
client.on('messageCreate', (message) => {
  if (message.content === '!ban') {
    // Ban the user
    message.member.ban();
    message.reply('User banned!');
  }
});

// Login to Discord with your bot token
client.login('YOUR_BOT_TOKEN');
```
This code will ban the user who sends the '!ban' message and respond with a message saying "User banned!".

**Setting up slash commands:**

1. Add the following code to your `index.js` file:
```javascript
const { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require('discord.js');

// Create a new client instance
const client = new Client({
  intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds, GatewayIntentBits.Messages]
});

// Register a new command
client.commands = new Map();
client.commands.set('ban', {
  description: 'Bans the user',
  execute: (interaction) => {
    interaction.member.ban();
    interaction.reply('User banned!');
  }
});

// Event listener for interactions
client.on('interactionCreate', (interaction) => {
  if (!interaction.isCommand()) return;

  const command = client.commands.get(interaction.commandName);
  if (!command) return;

  command.execute(interaction);
});

// Login to Discord with your bot token
client.login('YOUR_BOT_TOKEN');
```
This code will register a new slash command called `/ban` with a description and an execute function. When a user runs the `/ban` command, the bot will ban the user and respond with a message saying "User banned!".

**Note:** You need to restart your bot for the changes to take effect.

That's it! You should now have a working Discord bot that can ban users and respond to slash commands.

